<item>
            <title>[LU-3265] nrs_crrn_quantum proc files unreadable, sanity test_133f fails to detect this</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3265</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The nrs_crrn_quantum files are failing to read with -ENODEV probably because the fifo NRS is selected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;find ... -exec cmd ... \; ignores the return value of cmd. (This is not a bug, but is in accordance with the POSIX specification of find.) Hence the checks in 133f do not fail on unreadable files.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Two of the find invocations in test_133f still exclude req_history. That exclusion is no longer needed and should be removed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
